descripcion: FOX News Radio is a conservative radio station owned by Fox News Media. It supplies programming for two channels on Sirius XM and it is syndicated to several FM and AM radio stations across the USA. It is also possible to listen live to its broadcast worldwide via online live streaming. Launched in 2003, the station began as a provider of news updates to the syndicated radio stations, gradually increasing its broadcast time and teams of news reporters and radio professionals. Due to its success, the station began also offering talk shows on its line-up featuring well-known FOX News anchors and hosts. Currently, FOX News Radio syndicates three talk shows that are also available via live streaming: The Brian Kilmeade Show, The Guy Benson Show, and Fox News Across America with Jimmy Failla. The latter replaced Todd Starnes' show after his dismissal from Fox News in 2019. NPR (that stands for National Public Radio) is a non-profit radio station and media organization with an informative and educational intent. Its content is available via online live streams and podcasts and nationwide through the over 1000 public radio stations to which it serves as a national syndicator. Despite its non-profit status, it stands out as a public radio network as it was established by an act of Congress and the majority of the radio stations belong to its syndicated network belong to government entities. NPR is home to many of the most popular and listened-to radio programs in the USA as well as some of the most renowned news correspondents. Nina Totenberg (legal affairs correspondent), Avesha Rascoe (White House Reporter), Eleanor Beardsley (Europe/France correspondent), Sylvia Poggioli (Europe/Italy correspondent), Susan Stamberg (special correspondent), and Franco Ordoñez (White House correspondent) are only examples of well-known name to the US and global audiences.

Hot 97 FM was one of the first radio stations in the world offering programming focused on the Hip Hop scene and music. Being at the heart of the Hip Hop scene, the station has faced several controversies since its launch in the 40s and has often been the stage of many rivalries between artists as well as the cause of many feuds. The station is also renowned for its annual concenter series Summer Jam and for its segment Who’s Next that showcases and gives the floor to new and promising Hip Hop artists. The Ebro in the Morning show, hosted by DJs Ebro, Laura Stylez, and Rosenberg, has steadily remained the most popular and controversial station’s program for several years.

KUYI, also known as Hopi Radio, is a Native American public radio station. It caters to the Hopi, Tewa, and Navajo Native American tribes in Northern Arizona, offering locally produced content in line with the needs and interests of these communities. The station is also available globally via live streaming. KUYI went live on the airwaves for the first time at the end of 2000, with the goal of connecting the Native American communities and to bring the traditional Hopi storytelling to a wider audience, thus expanding its reach and awareness. The sign-call KUYI was chosen for its closeness to the Hopi word for water, 'Kuuyi', an important resource within the Hopi reservation. The station's daily schedule includes NPR programming as well as local and national news reports, cultural and educational shows about the traditions, arts, and language of the Hopi community, and talk shows in which guests and hosts discuss current and public affairs and how they affect the community.

During the day, it broadcasts local programming with talk shows focused on the most relevant issues for the Birmingham community. Its in-depth news reports also feature traffic and weather updates. At night, the air-time is taken by nationally syndicated shows such as the Mark Levin, Rush Limbaugh, or Ben Shapiro shows. Talk 99.5's broadcast is also available via online live streaming and podcasts. Main shows and personalities

Featuring a talented team of DJs and hosts, Simply Disco Radio delivers engaging content and lively discussions about the disco era. WBCQ FM, also known as Classic Country 94.7 Kixx FM, is a Classic Country radio station serving northern Maine and Western New Brunswick, Canada. It is owned by Allan Weiner, who also owns WBCQ-AM and WXME. Its weekly schedule features locally produced live shows in which the hosts light up the listener's mood with entertaining moments and promote local events and concerts, and music shows with the greatest classic country music by artists such as Waylon Jennings and Garth Brooks. The station also airs music shows dedicated to other music genres to keep its lineup varied and interesting. WBCQ FM additionally offers a live streaming service with no geographical restrictions to give people all over the world the opportunity to listen live to its programming and learn more about the communities in northern Maine. KYUK FM is a public radio station that serves the Yup'ik Eskimo community in the Yukon–Kuskokwim Delta (Southwestern Alaska).
